arts.ttl: Doncaster and AFC Wimbledon share spoils in battle for automatic promotion
arts.sum: Both teams finished the game with 10 men.

arts.ttl: AFC Wimbledon launch new three-episode documentary
arts.sum: Produced in collaboration with acclaimed author and Wimbledon supporter John Green and the Emmy Award-winning Mike Tollin Productions (MTP), whose relationship with the Dons began in 2016 when they released a short film about the club on VICE Sports, “Fan-Owned Football” underscores the club’s commitment to deepening its connection with its passionate members, as well as its ambition to reach a new generation of fans. “We are eternally grateful for the ongoing support of John Green and Mike Tollin Productions who have raised funding and produced the series, which included a significant donation to AFC Wimbledon.”

arts.ttl: AFC Wimbledon captain Jake Reeves: Automatic promotion race will go to the wire
arts.sum: “It’s extremely frustrating, but this happens most seasons,” Reeves told the South London Press. Walsall were runaway league leaders and had a 12-point gap to second place in January but have dropped to third, losing top spot for the first time in four months, after their 3-2 defeat to promotion rivals Port Vale on Saturday.

arts.ttl: Matty Stevens pens new two year contract with AFC Wimbledon
arts.sum: Stevens still had a season to go on his original Wimbledon deal but has been rewarded for his fine form. He has 17 League Two goals this season – four behind top scorer Michael Cheek – and has fired Johnnie Jackson’s side towards the top end of the table all season.
